-- NRG Buys Utility-Scale Guam Solar Project From Quantum Utility
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-07-15T16:46:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-15/nrg-buys-utility-scale-guam-solar-project-from-quantum-utility.html
NRG Energy Inc., the largest
independent U.S. electricity generator, acquired a utility-scale
solar project in Guam from Quantum Utility Generation LLC.  NRG will build, own and operate the 25.65-megawatt power
plant, which will sell electricity to the Guam Power Authority
under two 25-year agreements, the Princeton, New Jersey-based
company said in joint statement today. Terms of the sale were
not disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
